{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f9a9b970-8832-4920-b433-978cf9ead074","content":"You already have the HotReload extension referenced. To use it, run your tests with `dotnet test` in watch mode:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --hotreload\n```\n\nThis starts the test runner in a persistent session. When you edit your source or test files, it automatically re-runs affected tests **without a full rebuild**, giving you a fast feedback loop.\n\n**Workflow:**\n1. Run `dotnet test --hotreload` in a terminal\n2. Edit your code/tests to fix failures\n3. Save — tests re-run automatically\n4. Repeat until green\n\n> **Tip:** The `--hotreload` flag is provided by the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` package you already have. No additional configuration needed.\n\nWould you like me to run it now so you can start iterating on the failing tests?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"27512d5a-07a0-499d-b08c-c3aa0c3bb0aa","outputTokens":193,"requestId":"B445:1A3A99:DC9116:EAA636:6A044D59"},"id":"a969f73a-897b-41a8-88f0-c027225a9f96","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:07:28.517Z","parentId":"c3d2d647-e77e-4a54-9281-f6e6acc875f0"}
